Record Summary: “The Lord of the Rings Thread”

Core Exhibit (Observed in Gallery Real-Time Projection)

In the world of Middle-earth, the Dark Lord Sauron forges the
One Ring to rule them all. After its loss, the free peoples
face a final war as the Ring resurfaces in the hands of the
unlikeliest hero.

Governing Substrate: The Music of the Ainur — the world was
sung into being. Providence (often called “fate” or “the will
of the Valar”) works subtly through the choices of the humble. 

Power corrupts; mercy redeems. The Elder Days are fading; 
the Age of Men is dawning.

Key Peoples:
Hobbits: Simple, resilient, heart of the story.

Elves: Immortal, graceful, departing for the West.

Dwarves: Stout, proud, deep-delving.

Men: Varied kingdoms — noble Gondor, horse-lords of Rohan,
corrupted realms.

Wizards, Ents, Eagles, and darker forces: Orcs, Trolls, 
Nazgûl, Shelob.

Central Thread: The Fellowship of the Ring — Frodo Baggins, 
Samwise Gamgee, Gandalf, Aragorn, Legolas, Gimli, Boromir, 
Merry, and Pippin. The quest to destroy the Ring in the fires 
of Mount Doom.

Historical Cadence: 
Deep Empire Cycle → Rupture → Bloom across Ages. The Second 
Age ends with the Last Alliance; the Third Age culminates 
in the War of the Ring.

